24/04/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- In an interview Wednesday (23 April), Deputy Foreign Minister Andreas Loverdos said his country's Plan for Financial Reconstruction of the Balkans is proceeding as scheduled. Loverdos told MPA news agency there is no reason for concern and that the 550m euro programme will be completed by 2006 as expected. The plan aims to promote Balkan economies and encourage regional development. (MPA - 23/04/03)
